I think both countries share this need to think when this senseless loss of Humans stops. No doubt we have divided ourselves according to our ideological differences into two nations but above all we all are humans and share a severe need of peace and harmony.

I wish the day when there'd be soft borders between us, getting up in Lahore and spending my afternoon in Delhi. The day when I switch my TV on and there would be no news regarding human rights violations on any channel.

I want to see my people living and enjoying the '21st century freedom of life and freedom of speech' like rest of the world enjoying it. I want to see the Indo-Pak where Kashmiris feel safe to live in their neighborhood, where they don't have to suffer curfews.
